documentation.text:
XBR Payment/Paying Channel between a XBR data consumer and the XBR market maker,
 or the XBR Market Maker and a XBR data provider.
Event emittedd when a new XBR data market has opened.

Event emitted when payment channel is closing (that is, one of the two state channel
 participants has called "close()", initiating start of the channel timeout).

Event emitted when payment channel has finally closed, which happens after both state
 channel participants have called close(), agreeing on last state, or after the timeout
 at latest - in case the second participant doesn't react within timeout)
Instance of XBRMarket contract this contract is linked to.
Table of all XBR Channel closing states.

Constructor for this contract, only called once (when deploying the network).
 @param marketAdr The XBR markets contract this instance is associated with.

documentation.text:
Trigger closing this payment channel. When the first participant has called `close()`
 submitting its latest transaction/state, a timeout period begins during which the
 other party of the payment channel has to submit its latest transaction/state too.
 When both transaction have been submitted, and the submitted transactions/states agree,
 the channel immediately closes, and the consumed amount of token in the channel is
 transferred to the channel recipient, and the remaining amount of token is transferred
 back to the original sender.

params.account: The account to grant maintainer rights to.

params.marketAdr: The XBR markets contract this instance is associated with.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

returns._0: `true` if the account is maintainer, otherwise `false`.

params.actor: The actor (buyer/seller in the market) that opened this channel.
params.amount: The amount initially transfered to and held in the channel until closed.
params.channelId: The ID of the new XBR channel (must be unique).
params.ctype: Channel type: payment or paying channel.
params.delegate: The delegate (off-chain) allowed to spend/earn-on this channel (off-chain)  in the name of the actor (buyer/seller in the market).
params.marketId: The ID of the XBR market this channel is associated with.
params.marketmaker: The off-chain market maker executing the channel.
params.openedAt: Block number when the channel opening signature was created.
params.recipient: The receiver (on-chain) of the channel payout.
params.signature: EIP712 signature, signed by the member.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

Closed(uint8,bytes16,bytes16,uint256,uin.notice: Event emitted when payment channel has finally closed, which happens after both state channel participants have called close(), agreeing on last state, or after the timeout at latest - in case the second participant doesn't react within timeout)

Closing(uint8,bytes16,bytes16,uint256,ui.notice: Event emitted when payment channel is closing (that is, one of the two state channel participants has called "close()", initiating start of the channel timeout).

MaintainerAdded(address).notice: Event fired when a maintainer was added.

MaintainerRemoved(address).notice: Event fired when a maintainer was removed.

Opened(uint8,bytes16,bytes16,address,add.notice: Event emittedd when a new XBR data market has opened.

addMaintainer(address).notice: Add a new maintainer to the list of maintainers.

channelClosingStates(bytes16).notice: Table of all XBR Channel closing states.

closeChannel(bytes16,uint256,uint32,uint.notice: Trigger closing this payment channel. When the first participant has called `close()` submitting its latest transaction/state, a timeout period begins during which the other party of the payment channel has to submit its latest transaction/state too. When both transaction have been submitted, and the submitted transactions/states agree, the channel immediately closes, and the consumed amount of token in the channel is transferred to the channel recipient, and the remaining amount of token is transferred back to the original sender.

methods.constructor: Constructor for this contract, only called once (when deploying the network).

isMaintainer(address).notice: Check if the given address is currently a maintainer.

market().notice: Instance of XBRMarket contract this contract is linked to.

openChannel(uint8,uint256,bytes16,bytes1.notice: Open a new XBR payment/paying channel for processing off-chain micro-transactions.

userdoc.notice: XBR Payment/Paying Channel between a XBR data consumer and the XBR market maker, or the XBR Market Maker and a XBR data provider.
